{{Infobox organization |name= Association for the Study of Modern Italy |logo= |type=[[Non-profit]] |founded_date=1982 |founder=[[Christopher Seton-Watson]] |location=[[United Kingdom]], |origins= |area_served |focus=[[Italian Studies]] |method= |revenue= |endowment= |num_employees= |owner= |Non-profit_slogan= |homepage= [http://asmi.org.uk/]
}}
'''The Association for the Study of Modern Italy (ASMI)''' is the leading professional society in the United Kingdom for historians, political scientists, geographers, art historians, economists, and specialists in cultural, film and media studies working on nineteenth- twentieth- and twenty-first-century Italy. It was founded in 1982 by the distinguished historian of liberal Italy, [[Christopher Seton-Watson]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2007/dec/04/guardianobituaries.internationaleducationnews| title=Christopher Seton-Watson obituary - The Guardian}}</ref> and each year hosts a number of events including lectures, a postgraduate summer school and an international two-day conference. It also sponsors prizes and a variety of academic programmes and initiatives around the world devoted to the study of modern Italy. The themes of its annual conference have ranged from topics as diverse as migration, colonialism and law and order, to emotions, regionalism, the Italian crisis and war. It welcomes members of all countries.
==''Modern Italy''==
'''''Modern Italy''''' <ref>{{cite web|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayJournal?jid=MIT| title=Modern Italy - official page}}</ref> is the journal of the Association. It is one of the leading journals of [[Italian Studies]] and it publishes peer-reviewed academic articles across a broad range of disciplines. ''Modern Italy'', which is currently published by Cambridge University Press, is issued four times a year.
==Organisation== The association has an elected executive committee,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asmi.org.uk/about/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070429205854/http://www.asmi.org.uk/about/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2007-04-29|title=Members of the ASMI Executive Committee}}</ref> with a Chair, Secretary, and Treasurer. Previous Chairs have included [[Denis Mack Smith]], Professor [[John F. Pollard|John Pollard]], Professor Russell King, Professor David Forgacs, Professor Perry Willson, Professor Stephen Gundle and Professor [[Christopher Duggan (historian)|Christopher Duggan]]. The current Chair is Professor Lucy Riall.
