{{use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{infobox organization | name = Technical Image Press Association | image = | alt = | caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | abbreviation = TIPA | motto = | formation = {{start date and age|1991|4|16|paren=yes}}{{where|date=August 2015}} | founder = | founding_location = {{data missing|date=August 2015}} | type = [[International nongovernmental organization]] | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = [[Trade association]] | headquarters = [[Madrid]], [[Spain]] | location = | coords = {{coord|40.4501|-3.7726|region:ES_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | region = Worldwide | services = | fields = | membership = Photography and imaging magazines | membership_year = | language = English | leader_title = Chairman | leader_name = Thomas Gerwers | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = Board of directors | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|tipa.com}} }} The '''Technical Image Press Association''' ('''TIPA''')<ref name="website">[http://www.tipa.com Technical Image Press Association].</ref> is an international, [[non-profit]] association advocating the interests of the [[photography]] and imaging [[magazine]]-publishing industry.
The association represents 30 titles, published in eight European countries and seven non-European countries.
==History== The organization was established in 1991 as an association of European photography and imaging magazines. Since 2009, members have joined from outside of Europe.<ref name="history">[http://www.tipa.com/english/people.html "Board Members"]. Technical Image Press Association.</ref>
==Activities== Each year, the editors of the member magazines vote for the best products introduced to the market during the previous twelve months, taking into account innovation, cutting-edge technology, design, ease-of-use and the price to performance ratio of the products.<ref name="news">{{cite press release |url=http://www.photographymonthly.com/News-and-Reviews/2011/4/TIPA-Awards-2011 |title=TIPA Awards 2011 |date=21 April 2011 |website=Photography Monthly |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110424125024/http://www.photographymonthly.com/News-and-Reviews/2011/4/TIPA-Awards-2011 |archive-date=24 April 2011}}</ref>
TIPA holds its awards ceremony every second year<ref name="directory">[http://www.photostartsheet.com/photographic-associations.html Photo associations]</ref> at [[photokina]], a biennial trade fair for the photographic and imaging industries.
==Member magazines==
The member magazines that form TIPA are: {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * ''[[Camera (Australian magazine)|Camera]]'' – [[Australia]] * ''[[FHOX]]'' – [[Brazil]] * ''[[Photo Life]]'' – [[Canada]] * ''[[Photo Solution]]'' – [[Canada]] * ''[[Chinese Photography]]'' – [[China]] * ''{{ill|Fisheye (magazine)|lt=Fisheye|fr}}'' – [[France]] * ''{{ill|Réponses Photo|fr}}'' – [[France]] * ''[[digit!]]'' – [[Germany]] * ''[[Foto Hits Magazin]]'' – [[Germany]] * ''[[INPHO Imaging and Business]]'' – [[Germany]] * ''[[Photo Presse]]'' – [[Germany]] * ''{{ill|Photographie|de|Photographie (Magazin)}}'' – [[Germany]] * ''{{ill|ProfiFoto|de}}'' – [[Germany]] * ''[[Photo Business]]'' – [[Greece]] * ''[[Photographos]]'' – [[Greece]] * ''[[Fotó Magazin]]'' – [[Hungary]] * ''[[Better Photography]]'' – [[India]] * ''[[Fotografia Reflex]]'' – [[Italy]] * ''[[FOTOgraphia]]'' – [[Italy]] * ''[[Fotografie F+D]]'' – [[Netherlands]] * ''[[Fotovisie]]'' – [[Netherlands]] * ''[[P/f Professionele Fotografie]]'' – [[Netherlands]] * ''[[PiX Magazine]]'' – [[South Africa]] * ''[[FV / Foto-Vídeo Actualidad]]'' – [[Spain]] * ''[[Digital Photo]]'' – [[United Kingdom]] * ''[[Practical Photography]]'' – [[United Kingdom]] * ''[[Professional Photo]]'' – [[United Kingdom]] * ''[[photo District News|pdn]]'' – [[United States]] * ''[[Rangefinder (magazine)|Rangefinder]]'' – [[United States]] * ''[[Shutterbug (magazine)|Shutterbug]]'' – [[United States]] {{div col end}}
;Affiliate member * [[Camera Journal Press Club]] – [[Japan]]
==Administration== TIPA is supported by a board of directors and a [[wikt:secretariat|secretariat]] based in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]]. The board is elected by members at a [[general meeting]] held every year.
