{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox artwork | image_file = Da.se.ne.zaboravi.jpg | painting_alignment = right | image_size = 300px | title = Interrupted Flight | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Miodrag Živković (sculptor)|Miodrag Živković]] | year = {{start date|1953}} | type = Sculpture | height_metric = | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | dimensions = | metric_unit = cm | city = [[Kragujevac]], {{flag|Serbia}} | museum = | coordinates = | owner = }} '''October in Kragujevac Memorial Park''' ({{lang-sr|italic=yes|Spomen-park „Kragujevački oktobar"}}, Спомен-парк „Крагујевачки октобар"), also known as '''Šumarice Memorial Park''' (''Memorijalni park Šumarice'', Меморијални парк Шумарице), is the site near [[Kragujevac]], [[Serbia]] of the [[Kragujevac massacre|execution of an estimated 3,000 men and boys]] of the town by the [[Germany|German]] occupation forces on October 21, 1941, during [[World War II]].
According to noted historian [[Philip J. Cohen]], "All males from the town between the ages of sixteen and sixty were assembled and the victims -- including high school students -- were selected from among them."<ref>Philip. J. Cohen, "Serbia's Secret War", p.38</ref>
[[Monument]]s within the [[park]] include the monument to the murdered schoolchildren and their teachers (the "Interrupted Flight" monument); the "Monument of pain and defiance"; the "One hundred for one" monument; the "Resistance and Freedom" monument, and the monument to shoe cleaners.
The 21 October Museum is located at the site of the massacre.
